# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the values are
#   specific to the developer's system of choice, but for an application, they can be useful.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different python versions, they may encounter
#   dependency resolution issues. So, choosing to ignore Pipfile.lock is up to you.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies, but it is recommended to
#   version control it in most cases.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Poetry and Pipenv, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#pdm.lock

